    "recap_headline": "",
    "recap_text": "HUNTSVILLE \u2013\nThe Sam Houston Bearkats' ninth-inning rally came up just short in a 3-1 loss to Jax State in the series opener on Friday night at Don Sanders Stadium.\nSam Houston (8-9, 0-1 CUSA) trailed the Gamecocks (15-3, 1-0 CUSA) 3-0 after five innings, but got a run back in the seventh and loaded the bases in the ninth before reliever Skyler Hutto struck out pinch hitter\nEaston Dean\nto close out his fourth save of the year.\nRyan Franden\nmade his return to the lineup and singled in his final two at-bats of the game, including a 1-out base hit in the ninth to start the rally.\nHunter Alvord\nfollowed with a single and\nCade Corcoran\nlater walked before Hutto finished it off.\nStaff ace\nRyan Peterson\ntook his third loss of the year, despite striking out eight hitters in 5.0 innings of work. But he was matched by JSU starter Eli Pillsbury who struck out six and did not issue a walk in 6.2 frames to move to 3-0 on the year. He retired the first 13 Bearkats he faced before the Kats finally got a runner on the basepaths on a catcher's interference in the fifth.\nPeterson had already struck out five hitters in the first two frames before Luke Williams got the Gamecocks on the board when he led off the third with a solo homer to right field. Two innings later a single, bunt and error set JSU up for more offense and the Gamecocks capitalized with runs on a sacrifice fly and a double to left field.\nThe Kats threatened with runners in scoring position in both the fifth and sixth innings but could not push anything across until the seventh when Corcoran lined an RBI single into left-center field to score Franden.\nUP NEXT\nSam Houston will look to even the series with Jax State on Saturday with first pitch set for 2:00 p.m."
